      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what \"indemnification\" means. can u explain it in plain english?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is a promise to cover the other party's losses if something goes wrong. It means if you agree to indemnify someone, you're essentially saying, \"If a third party sues because of something I did while working on this contract, I'll take responsibility and pay for their legal costs and any damages.\" It's a way to shift potential financial risk between the parties.",
      "source": "target",
