      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically i want to make sure i'm not responsible for things that are totally out of my control or just random accidents. are there any other ways to protect myself from these kinds of unexpected threats or liabilities in a contract?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, you can add a \"Limitation of Liability\" clause, which caps the maximum amount of money you could ever be liable for. Another key protection is a \"Force Majeure\" clause, which excuses you from performance if something truly unavoidable happens, like a natural disaster. Finally, ensuring the scope of your work is very clearly defined prevents ambiguity that could lead to unexpected claims.",
      "source": "target",
